body:
Stayin alive

Let’s talk about how expensive it is to stay alive.


I have a full time, benefitted job. Those benefits have a 60 day waiting period. Unfortunately, because we value companies more than people, it seems entirely normal/average to have an employee wait MONTHS for insurance.


My “stay alive” necessary blood thinner is $498.52 without insurance. Almost double my car payment. It’s 60 capsules. $8.30 a capsule. With TWO “coupon” cards, I paid a total of $425.36. Bringing it down to $7.08 per capsule.


I cannot buy them individually, I am unable to buy half, and I don’t qualify for Marketplace with my new position/benefits being “available” to me.


So I have a question: how about instead of telling me what to do with my body, you help push through and encourage legislatures to hold pharmaceutical, health insurance, and companies as a whole accountable for price gouging and inflation just for profit? Be that kind of pro life. Because if you’re not, you’re pro-forced birth; nothing else.

summary: The Biblical Text Used to Support the Use of Cannabis. Purportedly the Bible supports the use of all the various seeds and herbs...
text: The Biblical Text Used to Support the Use of Cannabis. Purportedly the Bible supports the use of all the various seeds and herbs because they were created and blessed by God and could not be wrong to use. Consequently, the plant called hemp is proper for Christians to use for food, medicine, and enjoyment (Gen. 1:12).2 In Genesis 1:29–31, the Bible further indicates that all herbs are given for food.3 Much is made about the statement, found in the KJV, which supposedly speaks of hemp being the plant spoken of in Ezekiel 34:29, called a “plant of renown,” which would heal (Rev. 22:1–2)

summary: The Three Healing Pillars with Danette May
title: The Three Healing Pillars with Danette May
body:
After losing her son during childbirth, Danette found herself in a deep depression. The depression worsened when her marriage ended in a divorce and she found herself raising her two daughters alone.

Finding herself with $47 to her name, she recalls scouring through drawers looking for loose change, Danette knew she was meant for more.

It was then that she decided to stop being a victim and rewrite her story. She began to focus on the three pillars of healing: healing foods, healing movement, and a healing mindset.

These three pillars form the foundation of every product or program she’s created since then. With this simple philosophy, she transformed her life from having $47 to her name and operating as a single mother, to owning a $20 million dollar business helping women around the world. ;

Join in today and learn how Danette LEVELED UP and created EVERYTHING from NOTHING

In this episode, you will learn:

  • The process to healing your trauma
  • How to use the same pillars to grow a business
  • How to manifest what it is you want
  • What is manifestation…really

The post The Three Healing Pillars with Danette May appeared first on Natalie Jill Fitness.



source https://www.nataliejillfitness.com/the-three-healing-pillars-with-danette-may/

title: Controlling appetite? via /r/Fitness
body:
What’s the best way to control your appetite? I have this problem where if there is food around without thinking about it I’ll grab a bite and wat it. And once I start snacking I can’t stop throughout the day. Bit if I’m fasting and I don’t eat at all I’m good. I can go without just fine. But as soon as I eat something without even thinking I’ll keep returning to that and keep snacking.
